article.description: Elena Delle Donne had 30 points and 13 rebounds, and No. 22 Delaware pulled away to beat Wake Forest 70-57 on Sunday.
article.headline: Elena Delle Donne's 30 points lead Delaware by Wake Forest
article.linkText: Delle Donne's 30 lead Delaware by Wake Forest
article.story:
WINSTON-SALEM, N.C. --  Elena Delle Donne had 30 points and 13 rebounds, and Delaware (No. 25 ESPN/USA Today, No. 22 AP) pulled away to beat Wake Forest 70-57 on Sunday.

Delle Donne, who leads the nation with a 29-point average, helped the Blue Hens (8-0) claim their first win over an Atlantic Coast Conference team and extend the best start in school history.

Delaware held Wake Forest without a field goal for 11½ minutes during the decisive 19-3 run. Delle Donne's jumper with just over 11 minutes left made it 48-46 and put the Blue Hens ahead to stay. Jocelyn Bailey capped the burst with a free throw that put Delaware up 65-49 with 3:08 to play.

Chelsea Douglas scored 15 points for the Demon Deacons (7-2), and Secily Ray's layup with just under 14 minutes left tied it at 46. They didn't make another field goal until Douglas' 3-pointer with 2½ minutes remaining.
